-- ComplexNumber/trigonometric_identities.math
--
-- The first trigonometric identities, harvested from the functional
-- equation of the complex exponential and conjugation:
--
--   exp(i·x) · conj(exp(i·x)) = exp(i·x) · exp(−i·x) = exp(0) = 1,
--
-- whose real part is cos²x + sin²x = 1 (the Pythagorean identity),
-- and whose modulus form says |exp(i·x)| = 1: the exponential walks
-- the unit circle. Splitting exp(i·(x+y)) = exp(i·x)·exp(i·y) by
-- coordinates gives the addition formulas.

module ComplexNumber.trigonometric_identities

